The paper deals with the construction of binary codes that enable reliable communication in the presence of worst-case additive errors. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of efficient encoding and decoding algorithms, which could be categorized under data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the existence of such codes based on list decoding and certain algebraic manipulation detection codes, which could be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
